{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The review input is scoped to the lines that changed, not the full content of each modified file.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The failure boundary is the handoff between diff extraction and review-input assembly. A unit test of one parser function can miss bugs where another module re-expands to full file content.","test_description":"Use a fixture PR diff where unchanged lines contain obvious issues and changed lines are clean. Run the local diff-reader + prompt-builder together (no network). Assert the constructed review input contains only changed hunks and excludes unchanged file sections.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.35,"Integration":0.55,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Inline comments are attached to the correct positions in the diff view on the pull request.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Correct placement depends on real GitHub diff-position semantics and API behavior. Mocks can accept invalid/shifted coordinates that fail or render incorrectly on the real PR.","test_description":"Create a real test PR with known changed lines. Run inline-comment posting against GitHub, then fetch posted review comments and verify each path/line/side maps to the intended changed line in the PR diff.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.2,"System":0.75,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.03}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The agent identifies at least one real defect in a pull request that contains a known introduced bug.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"This is model-quality behavior: correctness depends on real LLM output and can vary run to run. Deterministic mocks cannot expose true miss-detection risk.","test_description":"Use a PR fixture with a deliberately introduced bug (ground truth labeled). Run the real model review repeatedly and assert at least one true-positive defect is identified at an acceptable hit rate threshold.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.06,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.8,"Workflow":0.1}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"Every finding listed in the top-level summary corresponds to an inline comment that was also posted — no findings appear in the summary without a matching inline comment.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"If summary text is model-generated, real failures include hallucinated findings not tied to posted inline comments. That failure is hidden by deterministic stubs.","test_description":"Run real finding generation and summary generation with a captured set of successfully posted inline comments. Parse summary findings and assert each maps to an existing inline comment ID/location.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.35,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.55,"Workflow":0.07}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The full sequence — reading the diff, posting inline comments, posting the summary comment — completes correctly for a real pull request without manual intervention.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"This is an end-to-end agent pipeline across multiple steps with real external systems and at least one agentic decision stage. The real failure boundary is the whole orchestrated flow.","test_description":"Execute the production entrypoint on a real sandbox PR. Verify all stages succeed in one unattended run: diff read, inline comments posted, summary posted, and summary-to-inline consistency checks pass.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.02,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.12,"Workflow":0.78}}]}
